	<td width="501" align="RIGHT" valign="TOP">
		
	
	<table width="95%" border="0" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0">
	
	<tr>
		<td><font face="Arial" size="3" color="#078D10"><b>HolyGoat</b></font></td>
		<td></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td><font face="Arial" size="2"><p>*** Now talking in #aninterview </p>

 <p>AN: Hello mate<Br>
 <i>HG: Lo :) </i><br>
 AN: Thanks for lking to AN<br>
 <i>HG: My pleasure. </i><Br>
 AN: So, you are working on ActionUT along with the A team<br>
 <i>HG: That`s right.</i> </p>

 <p><b>AN: What sort of mod are you aiming for? </b><br>
 AN: The action style or the slower CS type<br>
 <i>HG: We`re aiming to continue the feel of the previous mods; realistic running speed (slower than UT`s - roughly AHL`s), but dives and the like will keep things moving. <br>
An evolution of the previous mods.</i> <br>
AN: Right</p>

 <p><b>AN: Is there gonna be anything really new and exiciting from AUT for us :D</b><br>
 <i>HG: Customisable models. It`s pretty much certain that you`ll be able to pick your hats, cigars, trenchcoat length, etc. - and teams won`t be one model, they`ll be themed. <br>
So you can have all of the Reservoir Dogs if you want! </i><br>
AN: Wow<br>
That sounds impressive<br>
<i>HG: Oddjob`s a pretty good modeller ;) </i></p>

 <p><b>AN: So why have you chosen to develop AUT rather than AQ3? </b><br>
<i>HG: There`s a whole bunch of reasons. Firstly there are the engine reasons: better model support, nice detail textures, larger levels, inbuilt game type support, better scripting. Secondly, there`s the community reason. The UT community is a bit nicer than the Quake community in my current experience, and thirdly Epic are great guys :) </i><br>
AN: Are you working with Epic then? <br>
 <i>HG: They`re giving us support. In fact, they`re helpful to all mod groups - a big contrast to our experience with id. <br>
They`re as nice as Valve, if not more so :) </i><br>
AN: :) </p>

<p><b>AN: In the latest version of CS we have seen 2 new modes of play, does AUT plan anything of that description?</b> <br>
 <i>HG: If you check AHL Beta3, you`ll notice that we`ve got a very advanced goal-based game play system - you can do things that put TF to shame. <br>
Anything from hostages to bomb-defusal to just custom teams.<br>
Something similar is planned for AUT. </i><br>
AN: Is AHL beta 3 out yet then? <br>
<i>HG: It`ll be out pretty shortly. </i><br>
AN: Right<br>
<i>HG: I`m not going to give a precise date of course :) </i><br>
AN: Thought I`d missed something there :D</br>
<i>HG: :) </i></p>
 
 <p><b>AN: What about weaponary, will AUT have an enourmous catalougue of weapons for us to choose from</b><br>
 <i>HG: We`re not releasing our weapon specs at the moment. We will, of course, have nice guns while still keeping it balanced. </i><br>
 AN: How do you plan to keep it balanced....an infamously tricky task<br>
 <i>HG: Similar methods to those we`re employing in AHL... you can turn much quicker if you`re holding a pistol than if you`re holding a big rifle. Things like that. <br>
As well as conventional ammo methods and the like. </i><br>
AN: Hmm, thats a nice touch</p>

<p><b>AN: How long can we expect to wait for AUT then? </b><br>
 <i>HG: Heh. Until it`s done :) </i><br>
 AN: :/ <br>
 <I>HG: =)</i><br>
 AN: Git<br>
 <i>HG: Heheh. You should know me better than that :) </i><br>
 AN: :D</p>

 <p><b>AN: Will we be seeing an Asylum for AUT? </b><br>
 AN: Or are you working on better things? <br>
 <i>HG: Oooh... I`ll have to think about it :) I`ll get my first one or two out of the way, then see what develops :) <br>
 That`s almost certainly a `yes` =) </i><br>
 AN: I guessed :) <br>
 Right<br>
 <i>HG: Anything else? :) </i><br>

 <p><b>AN: If I only had enough room for AUT or another UT mod, why should i choose AUT? (this is where you get your final plug)</b> <br>
 <i>HG: Well, because you love Action, it`ll be fast paced, fun, cinematic, stylish, beautiful and it`ll get rid of fine lines and wrinkles in only 7 days. </i><br>
 AN: :D<br>
 I`ll get AUT for my mums birthday then<br>
 <i>HG: =)<br>
 Or Mother`s Day, start of April IIRC :) </i><br>
 AN: And finally</p>
 
<p><b>AN: Will AUT start (or finish) killing of AQ2? </b><br>
 <i>HG: I`m not sure on that count. The AQ2 community is pretty resilient, but a lot of them have expressed interest in AUT (probably because they didn`t like HL`s engine, or they wanted strafe jumps!). Every new game takes a chunk out of the community, but as long as they enjoy it, it doesn`t really matter what they play. </i><br>
 AN: As long as you dont leave us with an unfinished beta3 (ahem) im sure AUT will be a great step forward <br>
 Thankyou for you time<br>
 <i>HG: :) <br>
Thank you. </i><br>
 AN: Let us know when to expect AUT then<br>
 <i>HG: I`ll drop you a line. </i><br>
* Trin¦away goes to figure out how to post interviews on AN<br>
 <i>HG: :) </i></p>
 
<p>*** Quits: HolyGoat (-eXtreme- "640K ought to be enough for anybody." - Bill Gates, 1981)</p>


</font></td>
	</tr>
	
